OL,7,FThe group of women born in the 1950s
OL,8,Fknown as "women" (Women Against State
OL,9,FPension Inequality), say the rise in
OL,10,Fthe state pension age in 1995 led them
OL,11,Fto suffer financially.
OL,13,FThe 1995 Pensions Act and subsequent
OL,14,Flegislation raised the state pension
OL,15,Fage for women born on or after April 6
OL,16,F1950 from 60 to 65, then further to 66
OL,17,F- making it the same as the men's
OL,18,Fstate pension age.
